Reasoning: The paper deals with stochastic processes on graphs, specifically coalescing random walks. This topic falls under the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the consensus time in undirected graphs, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). The analysis of coalescence time involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are also relevant to the sub-category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper provides bounds on hitting time and cover time of regular graphs, which are topics in stochastic processes and statistical inference (cs.SI).
